column5: Not a walleye, but a muskie. I love this picture.
I caught this one a few years ago on Lake of the Woods.

Post a Pic of your smallest walleye or pike. Include any comments if you would like. Dock fishing in chamberlain narrows when I reeled in (unknowingly) this monster. I didnt measure it but guessing about 9-10 inches. Lipped him because he really didn't have many chompers yet!

Here are pics of a couple of my buddies from a 2002 trip. It takes *real* talent to catch fish like this! The walleye was about 5" and the smallie about 3". Both were barely able to get the jig in their mouths. I may have beat them in the biggest fish contest, but they certainly beat me when it came to finesse.81Saluki
Does Canada have thier version of DCFS? Abusing these children has to stopI caught my smallest walleye this year under the chin, probably couldn't get the minnow in his mouth, about 4in long!
The kids love when we get a baby.
Here's some good ones. The 2nd one isn't a walleye but thought it was funny considering the muskie lure was bigger than the perch.
it's harder to hook these than the big ones! phish
Caught a tiger musky about 20 yrs ago around that size ...still have the pic somewhere but it was way before digital cameras
Here's a walleye I caught on a jig & minnow while ice fishing at the NW Angle, LOTW...
Sort of reminds me of when I used to bow hunt for carp. I always felt that anyone could shoot a big one - it was the tiny ones that required the most skill! Bill Krejca
